<HEAD>US Experts Oppose Readmitting Soviets to Psychiatric Association</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By BRYAN BRUMLEY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Soviet efforts to curb psychiatric abuse, including an independent monitoring commission, are not enough to warrant readmitting <LOCATION> Moscow </LOCATION> to the <ORGANIZATION> World </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Psychiatric </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> experts say. The Soviets recently acknowledged that political and religious dissidents were incarcerated in psychiatric institutions _ a <LOCATION> Western </LOCATION> charge they long denied _ and in an unusual move sent a diplomat to <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> on Monday to testify about their reforms. The Soviet `` All-Union Scientific Society of Psychiatrists ... is doing its utmost to implement and translate into reality the needed reforms in the field of medical care and psychiatric health,'' said <PERSON> Georgi </PERSON> <PERSON> Markosov </PERSON>, a counselor at the Soviet Embassy. `` To prevent the use of psychiatry for non-medical purposes as well as to assure maximum openness in specific cases of misuse of psychiatry, an independent commission has been established, which is composed of eight persons,'' <PERSON> Markosov </PERSON> told the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> on </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Energy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commerce </ORGANIZATION> subcommittee on health and the environment. `` The commission is independent from the <ORGANIZATION> Health </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> or any -LRB- Communist -RRB- Party or state organs,'' he said, reading a statement from the Soviet psychiatric society. Before this year, it was rare for Soviet officials to testify before <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION>, but since January, about a half-dozen have done so. Despite the Soviets' effort to present their best case for readmission to the <ORGANIZATION> World </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Psych