GANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Washington </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> professor who was a member of the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> delegation that visited the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> this year. `` It remains to be seen whether it is indeed vigorous and independent,'' said <PERSON> Reddaway </PERSON>. The <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Psychiatric </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION>, which supported the work of the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> delegation, has voted to oppose readmission of the Soviet group to the world body, which is scheduled to meet in <LOCATION> Athens </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Greece </LOCATION>, on Oct. 11-16. The world body condemned Soviet practices in 1977 and the Soviets withdrew in 1983, facing almost certain expulsion. `` It is my sincere hope as well as the hope of the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Psychiatric </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> that there will be a time in the near future when we can wholeheartedly welcome the <ORGANIZATION> All-Union </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Society </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Psychiatrists </ORGANIZATION> and Narcologists of the <ORGANIZATION> USSR </ORGANIZATION> into the <ORGANIZATION> World </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Psychiatric </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION>,'' testified <PERSON> Ellen </PERSON> <PERSON> Mercer </PERSON>, head of international programs for the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> organization. `` It is also our concern that, unfortunately, this time has not yet arrived,'' <PERSON> Mercer </PERSON> said. Soviet health officials who in the past sent dissidents to psychiatric institutions remain in senior government posts, said <PERSON> Reddaway </PERSON>, and they could resume their abuses if there is a conservative reaction along the lines of the crackdown in <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> this summer. The officials he mentioned were <PERSON> Yevgeny </PERSON> <PERSON> Chazov </PERSON>, the health minister; <PERSON> Nikolai </PERSON> <PERSON> Zharikov </PERSON>, last year appointed the head of the <ORGANIZATION> Soviet </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Society </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Psychiatrists </ORGANIZATION> and Narcologists; <PERSON> Georgy </PERSON> <PERSON> Morozov </PERSON>, who for decades has headed the <ORGANIZATION> Serbsky </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Institute </ORGANIZATION> where many political dissidents have been held in psychiatric care, and <PERSON> Alexander </PERSON> <PERSON> Churkin </PERSON>, chief psychiatrist of the ministry of health.
