tock exchange, `` The rebound of the dollar did n't do much to help the sentiment of the market,'' said a dealer at <ORGANIZATION> Kleinwort </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Benson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION>, who spoke on condition of anonymity. He said many investors were sitting on the sidelines watching the currency markets. `` Many people seemed content to lock in the short-term gains of the past few days,'' he said, referring to sales for profit-taking. Stocks that were strong last week, including securities, insurance, railway and retailer sales issues, fell back. Shares in some smaller companies and warehousing firms rose strongly. `` It was n't all doom and gloom. It was mostly the big stocks that were being hit'' in the market's decline, the trader said.
