<HEAD>Black Tar Heroin Leads to Overdoses, Deaths</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By KATHLEEN MACLAY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A rash of overdoses and deaths attributed to particularly potent chips of `` black tar'' heroin has addicts and occasional users alike terrified and frantically seeking treatment, officials said. From Friday through Monday, three people died and dozens of others were treated after they literally were knocked off their feet and rendered unconscious after injecting themselves with the most-popular form of heroin in the drug world. `` It's the talk of the neighborhood,'' said <PERSON> Eddie </PERSON> <PERSON> Franks </PERSON>, director of the Facts on Crack program at Glide Memorial Church in the <LOCATION> Tenderloin </LOCATION> <LOCATION> district </LOCATION>, where most of the overdoses occurred. `` What we're here for now is prevention and support while this epidemic is going on,'' <PERSON> Franks </PERSON> said, adding that a 24-hour crisis telephone line has been set up and will operate as long as necessary. Police Inspector <PERSON> Sam </PERSON> <PERSON> Osborne </PERSON> said a dealer probably forgot to mix the heroin with other materials to dilute its strength, which normally is 6 percent to 9 percent pure. Tests showed the heroin had a 36 percent to 38 percent purity, said Lt. <PERSON> Jim </PERSON> <PERSON> Mollinari </PERSON>. Since overdose cases fell off sharply, he said, `` My guess is there's probably not much more out there.'' Black tar, named for its color and gooey appearance, has become the most commonly used heroin by <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Francisco </LOCATION>'s estimated 15,000 to 18,000 addicts since coming on the scene about seven years ago, said Dr. <PERSON> Alex </PERSON> <PERSON> Stalcup </PERSON>, medical director of the Haight-Ashbury Free Clinic. It sells for about $ 20 a bag that can be broken into several shots. The clinic generally treats about 120 people daily and turns away about 10 or 15. Within a couple of hours Monday, it had turned away almost 40, he said. `` The people who buy street heroin are literally playing with their lives,'' he said. The fatalities were said to be men ages 35, 41 and 43. The <ORGANIZATION> San </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Francisco </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Coroner </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Office </ORGANIZATION> did not release names. Last week, <ORGANIZATION> federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Drug </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Enforcement </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Administration </ORGANIZATION> agents seized 2 kilos of black tar heroin at hotels near <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Francisco </LOCATION> <LOCATION> International </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Airport </LOCATION>.
