<HEAD>New Commission to Boost U.S. Work Skills</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By LEE MITGANG</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Education Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A commission of business, union and political leaders announced on Tuesday plans to study ways to make <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> workers more competitive with those in other industrialized countries. The 34-member Commission on the Skills of the American Workforce will be chaired by <PERSON> Ira </PERSON> <PERSON> Magaziner </PERSON>, an international business authority, co-chaired by former <ORGANIZATION> Labor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Secretaries </ORGANIZATION> <PERSON> Bill </PERSON> <PERSON> Brock </PERSON> and <PERSON> Ray </PERSON> <PERSON> Marshall </PERSON>, and will include <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION> Gov. <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> <PERSON> Kean </PERSON> and the chief executives of <ORGANIZATION> Eastman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Kodak </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Corning </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Glass </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Works </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, and <ORGANIZATION> Apple </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Computer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co </ORGANIZATION>. The commission will study job skill development programs in seven countries: the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Sweden </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Denmark </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ireland </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Singapore </LOCATION>. According to <PERSON> Magaziner </PERSON>, the commission's final report, expected next spring, will: _ Urge changes in <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> secondary schools to ensure youngsters graduate with job skills, _ Call for a `` second chance system'' for those out of high school and out of work, and _ Urge creation of a system to update skills of existing <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> workers. `` The <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> is in a race with time. From <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION> to <LOCATION> Singapore </LOCATION>, those nations that are winning the economic war have made the development and effective use of very highly skilled work forces an indispensible part of their strategy,'' said <PERSON> Magaziner </PERSON>. `` The <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> knows it is far behind in the schooling process, but it has hardly begun to think about an equally pressing problem _ how to raise the skills of line workers already in the workforce,'' he said. Research is expected to take seven months, <PERSON> Magaziner </PERSON> said. The project will consist of more than 2,000 interviews with plant executives, employees and policymakers in those seven nations. It is being funded by a $ 250,000 grant from <ORGANIZATION> Carnegie </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>. The commission is an initiative of the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> on </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Education </ORGANIZATION> and the Economy, in <LOCATION> Rochester </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.Y. </LOCATION>, an organization founded in 1987 as an outgrowth of `` A Nation Prepared: Teachers for the 21st Century,'' a landmark Carnegie report widely credited with shifting <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> school reform toward empowering teachers and restructuring schools. <PERSON> Marc </PERSON> <PERSON> Tucker </PERSON>, author of that report, is president of the Rochester-based center. Besides <PERSON> Magaziner </PERSON>, <PERSON> Kean </PERSON>, <PERSON> Brock </PERSON> and <PERSON> Marshall </PERSON>, the commission will include: <PERSON> Morton </PERSON> <PERSON> Bahr </PERSON>, president, <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Workers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> America </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Carlough </PERSON>, president, <ORGANIZATION> Sheet </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Metal </ORG