id in a recent interview. `` Many of the really big acknowledged experts have potential conflicts. We need advice on how to sell real estate and the same contractors that would provide us advice ... are probably advising somebody else who may be interested in buying that real estate.'' The code prohibits contractors from self-dealing, favortism and conflicts of interest and sets up an agency board to rule on cases that are n't black and white In another safeguard, the management of the <ORGANIZATION> RTC </ORGANIZATION> is split in a unique arrangement designed to prevent abuse. Policies are formulated by a Cabinet-level board headed by <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> Secretary <PERSON> Nicholas </PERSON> <PERSON> F. </PERSON> <PERSON> Brady </PERSON>. But the actual operations are being carried out by the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Deposit </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Insurance </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, the independent agency insuring bank and <ORGANIZATION> S </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; L deposits, through a staff headed by <PERSON> Cooke </PERSON>. In the first few weeks of the <ORGANIZATION> RTC </ORGANIZATION>'s existence, that structure led to public squabbling between the <ORGANIZATION> FDIC </ORGANIZATION> and the adminstration oversight board. <PERSON> Cooke </PERSON> said the tension was easing, but members of <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> are still concerned. `` The one thing that's troubled me so far is the fighting between -LRB- the <ORGANIZATION> FDIC </ORGANIZATION> -RRB- and the -LRB- oversight -RRB- board. ... Is that really resolved permanently or is it just quiescent?'' said Rep. <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> Schumer </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-N.Y. </LOCATION>, a member of a <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> task force appointed to oversee the <ORGANIZATION> RTC </ORGANIZATION>. However, <PERSON> Cooke </PERSON>