<HEAD>Helms Urges Adding Authorizing Troops in Panama to Drug Bill</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: The Senate will not finish debate tonight, and the following
should stand for AMs</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MIKE ROBINSON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> became snarled late Tuesday in a fight over whether to authorize the use of <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> troops against Panamanian dictator <PERSON> Manuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON>, indicted in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> on drug trafficking charges, as it debated legislation to bolster the war on drugs. `` We had a golden opportunity to help the people of <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION> rid themselves of a malignancy,'' Sen. <PERSON> Jesse </PERSON> <PERSON> Helms </PERSON>, <LOCATION> R-N.C. </LOCATION>, said as he offered his plan. His offering came as senators churned through a wide-ranging bill that would add hundreds of new agents, federal marshals and prosecutors to the war on drugs and place care of crack addicts under the Medicaid program. `` These amendments will lay the groundwork for a new, expanded drug control strategy,'' <ORGANIZATION> Judiciary </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> R. </PERSON> <PERSON> Biden </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON>, D-Del., said as the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> approved the additions Senators planned to put the finishing touches on the bill Wednesday. <PERSON> Helms </PERSON>' proposal would authorize the president to `` use the armed forces of the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> to secure the removal of General <PERSON> Manuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Antonio </PERSON> <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> from his illegal control of the Republic of <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION>.'' <PERSON> Biden </PERSON> expressed concern about the measure, saying `` I wonder if it is so broad that we are authorizing the president to declare war.'' He said it was possible that `` the <LOCATION> Gulf </LOCATION> <LOCATION> of </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Tonkin </LOCATION> resolution might blush by comparison.'' The <LOCATION> Tonkin </LOCATION> resolution of 1965 led to es