ging from a study of the possibility of ending the use of disposable needles to earmarking forfeited drug funds to buy weapons and body armor for agents. `` We'll probably pass a lot of these things and then they will never see the light of day,'' said Sen. <PERSON> Orrin </PERSON> <PERSON> Hatch </PERSON>, <LOCATION> R-Utah </LOCATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> GOP </ORGANIZATION> floor leader. `` The <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> wo n't let it happen'' and the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> itself might have some second thoughts before final action, <PERSON> Hatch </PERSON> said.
