wires.</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By ROB WELLS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ROBINSON CREEK, Ky. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Windshields were smashed and tires flattened today on a picket line set up in support of the <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Workers </ORGANIZATION> strike against <ORGANIZATION> Pittston </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Coal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION>. More than 350 miners in <LOCATION> Kentucky </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION> walked out Monday at mines filling <ORGANIZATION> Pittston </ORGANIZATION> orders. At the <ORGANIZATION> Rob </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fork </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mining </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Police </ORGANIZATION> said `` jackrocks,'' or bent roofing nails welded together, were used to flatten the tires of at least three coal trucks, a management employee's pickup and a <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Police </ORGANIZATION> cruiser. Two passing coal trucks had windshields smashed. Nearly 200 men in camouflage congregated around the entrance to <PERSON> Rob </PERSON> <PERSON> Fork </PERSON>, where the strike affects 50 miners. As the crowd parted to allow foremen to drive through, a faint ringing could be heard as jackrocks dropped on the pavement. State Police said no immediate arrests were made. A striking miner was hit by a non-union coal truck attempting to cross a picket line Monday, but he was not seriously hurt. The incident set off a four-hour confrontation between miners and a convoy of non-union trucks poised to cross the line to unload their coal. The standoff ended with the trucks driving away. <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Police </ORGANIZATION> dispatched 38 troopers, but there were no arrests and no reported problems at other picket lines in <LOCATION> Kentucky </LOCATION> or <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION>. <ORGANIZATION> UMW </ORGANIZATION>