percent to 310,000 and were up 6.6 percent in the West to 244,000 units. The <ORGANIZATION> Commerce </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> report said the median price of a new home was $ 122,900 in August, up 6.0 percent from $ 116,000 in July. The median is the point where half of the homes sold for more and half for less. The average price of a new home rose 14.6 percent to $ 162,300.
