<DATELINE>BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> MGM </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Grand </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> said Tuesday it will spend $ 700 million to convert a <LOCATION> Las </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Vegas </LOCATION> golf course into a movie theme park and a 5,000-room hotel-casino, gambling on luring families to `` the best mouse trap in town.'' `` I remember the days when <LOCATION> Las </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Vegas </LOCATION> lived almost entirely on the high roller,'' <ORGANIZATION> MGM </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Grand </ORGANIZATION> chairman <PERSON> Fred </PERSON> <PERSON> Benninger </PERSON> said at a news conference at the <LOCATION> Beverly </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hills </LOCATION> Hotel. `` You ca n't do that anymore.'' The site is on the <LOCATION> Las </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Vegas </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION> location where the <ORGANIZATION> Tropicana </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Country </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Club </ORGANIZATION> and Marina Hotel and Casino now stand. <PERSON> Benninger </PERSON> would n't reveal how much MGM Grand paid for those properties. Other details were sketchy as well, although conceptual drawings showed towering spires and domes, like a futuristic version of Sleeping Beauty's Castle at <LOCATION> Disneyland </LOCATION>. MGM Grand, owned by <LOCATION> Beverly </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hills </LOCATION> billionaire <PERSON> Kirk </PERSON> <PERSON> Kerkorian </PERSON>, said last month it might build the theme park on a 60-acre site beside the <ORGANIZATION> Desert </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inn </ORGANIZATION>, which it owns and is promoting as a top-end hotel-casino. The new theme park site, at 115 acres, is nearly twice as large. <PERSON> Benninger </PERSON> said finding enough space was a more important consideration than money. The new MGM Grand Hotel and theme park are tentatively expected to open by late 1992. <PERSON> Benninger </PERSON> said he was confident the complex, with hotel rooms costing about $ 40 a night, would cash in on the trend toward family tourism in <LOCATION> Las </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Vegas </LOCATION> that began with the opening of Circus Circus a decade ago. Las Vegas will count more than 18 million visitors this year, up from 11 million in 1980. Its population has boomed from 300,000 eight years ago to more than 700,000. <LOCATION> Las </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Vegas </LOCATION> officials have said for years that the city needed a major theme park to help attract families. A water theme park, built on the <LOCATION> Las </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Vegas </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION> five years ago, has been extremely successful. `` Clearly the theme park idea is one that has been looked at for quite a while,'' said <PERSON> Harold </PERSON> <PERSON> Vogel </PERSON>, veteran entertainment analyst for <ORGANIZATION> Merrill </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lynch </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> `` It's an adult resort, and now they're going to extend it so the rest of the family members can enjoy it too. <PERSON> Benninger </PERSON> said movie themes had proved an enduring lure to tourists, as proved by expansions of <ORGANIZATION> Walt </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Disney </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> MCA </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Universal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Studios </ORGANIZATION> into <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> movie theme parks `` There has always been competition in <LOCATION> Las </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Vegas </LOCATION>,'' <PERSON> Benninger </PERSON> said. `` I'm not worried about competition. We're building the best mouse trap in town.'' <PERSON> Benninger </PERSON> said <ORGANIZATION> MGM </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Grand </ORGANIZATION> will add 4,300 rooms to the 700-room <PERSON> Marina </PERSON> at a cost of about $ 250 million. The theme park, which will cost about $ 450 million, will include a working film and television studio, although he said it might have just one sound stage. It is anticipated that the complex will employ 7,000 workers. Other details were sketchy. A name for the complex, and even its designers, have yet to be selected. <PERSON> Benninger </PERSON> would n't reveal details about the attractions being considered, although he said there were many. He said `` two or three organizations'' had approached him about possible partnerships and left open the possibility of finding another partner. <PERSON> Benninger </PERSON> said MGM Grand regarded the development as a prototype and had already received calls from unidentified organizations about developing similar complexes elsewhere. MGM Grand, a separate company from <ORGANIZATION> MGM-UA </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, owns an all-frills <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles-New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> airline as well as the Desert Inn. It also retains rights to a stylized version of the famous MGM lion. <PERSON> Kerkorian </PERSON>, 72, had sold and bought back bits and pieces of <ORGANIZATION> MGM-UA </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> for two decades, a period during which he also traded <LOCATION> Las </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Vegas </LOCATION> hotels the way most people buy cars. Then last month, <LOCATION> Australia </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Qintex </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> agreed to purchase <ORGANIZATION> MGM-UA </ORGANIZATION> _ including the original lion logo _ for $ 1.5 billion, outbidding media mogul <PERSON> Rupert </PERSON> <PERSON> Murdoch </PERSON> by $ 100 million. A fire at the original MGM Grand Hotel, which <PERSON> Kerkorian </PERSON> built in 1973, killed 84 people in 1980. In 1985, <PERSON> Kerkorian </PERSON> sold the hotel and it