<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Kaufman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Broad </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Home </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> said Tuesday it sold an office building complex in <LOCATION> Paris </LOCATION> for about $ 600 million, which it said was the biggest commercial real estate deal in French history. The complex, to be called <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Plaza </LOCATION>, is located on 2.2 acres near the Champs Elysee, a site where the <ORGANIZATION> Shell </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Oil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> currently has its French headquarters. The buyers were an international group of investors headed by <PERSON> Kowa </PERSON> Real estate, a unit of <ORGANIZATION> Industrial </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Japan </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Kaufman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> Broad </PERSON> said in a statement. <ORGANIZATION> Kaufman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Broad, a big <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> home builder, sells its commercial real estate projects in <LOCATION> France </LOCATION> before developing them. <ORGANIZATION> Kaufman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> Broad </PERSON> said it will renovate two facades in the existing <LOCATION> Paris </LOCATION> structure to retain the building's historical significance, and build five buildings totaling 560,000 square feet and five levels of underground parking. Construction is to begin in December 1990, when <ORGANIZATION> Shell </ORGANIZATION> moves out of the existing building, and should be completed by spring 1993, <ORGANIZATION> Kaufman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORG